Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper discusses the evolution of the Internet and proposes a new generation of the Internet, which is related to networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the transmission of information through the Tactile Internet, which could be related to information theory. 
3. cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) - The Tactile Internet could have security and privacy concerns, which could be related to cryptography and security. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The Tactile Internet could require new systems and control mechanisms to manage the communication between devices, which could be related to systems and control. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The development of the Tactile Internet could require new software engineering techniques and methodologies, which could be related to software engineering.
